OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Japan's Prime Minister Fumio Kishida   
OL,6, has been criticised for saying the     
OL,7, country's ban on same-sex marriage is  
OL,8, not discriminatory.                    
OL,10,FWeeks ago, he apologised to the LGBTQ  
OL,11,Fcommunity over homophobic comments made
OL,12,Fby an aide who has since been sacked.  
OL,14,FMr Kishida's party is under growing    
OL,15,Fpressure to improve LGBTQ rights, as   
OL,16,Fmore Japanese support same-sex         
OL,17,Fmarriage.                              
OL,19,FJapan remains the only G7 country that 
OL,20,Fdoesn't recognise such unions.         
